import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of population over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.barplot(x='sex', y='people', data=data, estimator=sum, ci=None)
    ax.set(xlabel='Gender', ylabel='Population')
    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, p: format(int(x), ',')))
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
